text:
Hi <@UUXLKS2F4>! Could you laser cut these three files when you come in to Nolop today? If you do not have time to cut all three, no worries, just let me know which ones you can cut! If you think the engraving parts will take too long, let me know and I can reduce the engraving area.

Units are in inches for all three. JoesJazzHourSign should be 8x8in and cut in 1/4" (or 1/8" if no 1/4") frosted acrylic (or 1/4" birch if there's no frosted acrylic left), KitzConsultingSign should be 6x9in and cut in 1/4" birch, and for Road_Trip the width of the outline of Massachusetts should be about 15.75in and the width of the car should be about 12.3 in and cut in 1/4" birch. Red is for cutting, black is for engraving, and blue is for etching. Thank you!
